Zanzan malitere ọrụ ya na-egwuri egwu maka JS du Ténéré na Niger Premier League na Satellite FC na Côte d'Ivoire, tupu ọ kwaga Belgium na 2002.
Zanzan gbara bọọlụ afọ isii na Belgian First Division, maka Germinal Beerschot, Lokeren na FC Brussels, ma gbaa bọọlụ na Romanian Liga I maka Otopeni, tupu ọ gaa n'ihu n'ọrụ ya na North America.
On April 15, 2009, Zanzan signed with Montreal Impact of the USL First Division. He played 12 games for the Canadian team before leaving at the end of November 2009
In 2012, he signed a contract at amateur team FC Eksaarde In Belgium
Zanzan anọwo na-arụ ọrụ mgbe niile na ndị otu mba Togo kemgbe 1999, ebe o mere nke mbụ ya mgbe ọ dị naanị afọ iri na itoolu
Ọ bụ otu n'ime ndị otu Togo na 2006 Africa Cup of Nations
